    <node id="Hub Diameter">
      <data key="d0">Hub Diameter</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hub Diameter is the measurement of the central part of the flange.&lt;SEP&gt;Hub Diameter is a technical dimension specifying the minimum diameter of the hub component in flange design.&lt;SEP&gt;Hub Diameter refers to the measurement of the hub component in Class 600 Flanges, specified in Table II-16.&lt;SEP&gt;Hub Diameter refers to a critical dimension of the flange, specifying the size of the hub.&lt;SEP&gt;Hub Diameter is a dimensional parameter specified for Class 1500 Flanges in Table II-20.</data>
