    <node id="Class 1500">
      <data key="d0">Class 1500</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Class 1500 is a pressure class associated with specific working pressures for materials in the pressure-temperature rating tables.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 1500 is a pressure rating category associated with specific dimensional measurements in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 1500 refers to a standard rating for pipe flanges and fittings, included in the pressure-temperature ratings and dimensional data appendix.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 1500 is a pressure rating category for pipe fittings, referenced in the table of groove dimensions.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 1500 refers to a type of flange specification used for dimensions in specific pipe sizes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5f3cbee2b8b675333577ec60e28d2c11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cea3562154969682c66ce990ace4317&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08f0e4ff5c7211b5aa229f22014500b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33ecf81d981808caaccea063cc37fe52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33579e7d70708dd13efea5c7aa88857f</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
