      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Class 2500 is a pressure class associated with specific working pressures for materials in the pressure-temperature rating tables.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 2500 refers to a standard rating for pipe flanges and fittings, included in the pressure-temperature ratings and dimensional data appendix.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 2500 is a pressure rating category for pipe fittings, referenced in the table of groove dimensions.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 2500 refers to a specific classification or standard for flange drilling templates mentioned in the text.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5f3cbee2b8b675333577ec60e28d2c11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cea3562154969682c66ce990ace4317&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08f0e4ff5c7211b5aa229f22014500b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1a0cc3f06b6ae74d626b324304f6636</data>
