    <node id="ASTM A217">
      <data key="d0">ASTM A217</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">ASTM A217 is a standard that prohibits the addition of certain elements to steel materials, except for calcium and manganese for deoxidation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-847b451bcebb49d1e06690a456dff19f</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776347057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Carbide Phase">
      <data key="d0">Carbide Phase</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Carbide Phase refers to a component in steel that may transform into graphite under specific high-temperature conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-847b451bcebb49d1e06690a456dff19f</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776347057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Graphite">
      <data key="d0">Graphite</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Graphite is a material form that the carbide phase of steel may convert to upon prolonged exposure to high temperatures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-847b451bcebb49d1e06690a456dff19f</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776347057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Deoxidation">
      <data key="d0">Deoxidation</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Deoxidation is a process involving the addition of calcium and manganese to steel materials as permitted by ASTM A217.&lt;SEP&gt;Deoxidation is a metallurgical process involving the addition of calcium (Ca) and manganese (Mn) to Group 1.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-847b451bcebb49d1e06690a456dff19f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4226f54789317bf6ebb818f32cbfcbe1</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776347057</data>
