    <node id="Pressure–Temperature Ratings">
      <data key="d0">Pressure–Temperature Ratings</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pressure–Temperature Ratings are technical specifications that define the maximum allowable working pressures for materials at different service temperatures, particularly in the context of pipe flanges and fittings. These ratings establish the operational limits of components under varying thermal and pressure conditions, ensuring safe and effective performance in industrial or engineering applications. They are typically presented in tabular formats, detailing pressure thresholds for specific materials across multiple temperature classes or ranges. The data is material-specific and often included in a Mandatory Appendix of relevant standards, providing critical information for selecting appropriate components based on their intended use. The tables may express values in both metric (bar/Celsius) and imperial (psi/Fahrenheit) units to accommodate diverse engineering requirements. Pressure–Temperature Ratings are essential for determining the suitability of materials and components in systems where temperature fluctuations could affect pressure integrity, such as in piping networks or mechanical equipment subjected to thermal stress.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-40eb7e383f01cd90cdcb3549885e2bf5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b3b2ad50e17452e4c5cdf246ea7c450e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94ad67236a04ed5e89ab9dc58f055492&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cea3562154969682c66ce990ace4317&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-647a44b09d06095cfa48fa8da04ad67a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e93d95d834a56048774bc1ff8730f33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08f0e4ff5c7211b5aa229f22014500b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8dbc1ca69385a5b0dc8a2e4f721251fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2610550c25acaed1b68e10f60397e039&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9189525fe5b68e50911a109b29537fe3</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776347087</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
