      <data key="d3">chunk-cf3f17b17790e2fe3d4ddd7686342236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d18cb2257a5c4112cbc867096f095fe</data>
      <data key="d2">The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns." So in this case, the pressure-temperature ratings (as data) are related to the groups (concepts).&lt;SEP&gt;The decline in the Global Tech Index is part of the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns." So they linked the index to the selloff. In this case, the pressure ratings are data points, so the relationship between the material and the temperature would have the pressure as a keyword. But the previous output might have missed some of these relationships. For example, in the first table, "25Cr–12Ni" is associated with "A351 Gr. CH8" and "A351 Gr. CH20". The previous extraction didn't include these relationships. So I need to add those.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776347087</data>
      <data key="d6" />
